name: r-keras
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "2.9.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-keras
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/keras_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/keras/keras_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: cc2392a49b8dcbbff8b774f08d714bb776231fa4a9f60136999d9deb421ba118

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-r6
    - r-ellipsis
    - r-generics >=0.0.1
    - r-glue
    - r-magrittr
    - r-reticulate >1.22
    - r-rlang
    - r-tensorflow >2.7.0
    - r-tfruns >=1.0
    - r-zeallot
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-r6
    - r-ellipsis
    - r-generics >=0.0.1
    - r-glue
    - r-magrittr
    - r-reticulate >1.22
    - r-rlang
    - r-tensorflow >2.7.0
    - r-tfruns >=1.0
    - r-zeallot

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('keras')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('keras')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://keras.rstudio.com
  license: MIT
  summary: Interface to 'Keras' <https://keras.io>, a high-level neural networks 'API'. 'Keras' was developed with a focus on enabling fast experimentation, supports both convolution based networks and recurrent networks (as well as combinations of the two), and runs seamlessly on both 'CPU' and 'GPU' devices.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - zamorarr
